                                                              <br/> 
                                <div class="phototagleft">
                                  
                                </div>
                                                          </div>
                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb"><strong>Mbizo Chirasha</strong>&nbsp;is the author of&nbsp;<em>A Letter to the President</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Pilgrims of Zame</em>&nbsp;and coauthor of multiple books. He is associate editor at&nbsp;<em>Diasporia(n)</em>&nbsp;online, chief editor at&nbsp;<em>Time of the Poet Republic</em>, founding editor at WomaWords Literary Press, publisher at&nbsp;<em>Brave Voices</em>&nbsp;poetry journal, and curator at Africa Writers Caravan. A contributing essayist to&nbsp;<em>Monk</em>, his poetry and writings appear in&nbsp;<em>FemAsia Magazine</em>,&nbsp;<em>Wrath-Bearing Tree</em>, and&nbsp;<em>Ink Sweat and Tears</em>.</p>
